* **Custom Prefix:** The default prefix key has been remapped to **`Ctrl-a`**.
* **VM Copy/Paste:** Hold `Shift` while highlighting text to use your host machine's normal cursor. This bypasses tmux's internal mouse mode, allowing you to easily copy and paste text directly out of a Virtual Machine environment.
```bash
tmux # start new session
tmux new -s work # start new session named work
tmux ls # lsit all sessions

tmux attach -t work # reattach to session named work
tmux a # attaches to most recent session

tmux kill-session -t work # kill session named work
tmux kill-server # kill everything all sessions

# From inside tmux
prefix + d # detach from current session, everything stays in the background
prefix  + s # show list of sessions
prefix + $ # rename current session
prefix + ( # prev session
prefix + ) # next session
prefix + : # open command prompt
```

